         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">July 9/69 ¶ My dear Müller ¶  ¶ I write in haste by this mail, &amp; chiefly to say that your assistant Theodore ¶  called 2 days ago on his way to Germany, having had his money stolen from him in Liverpo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.07.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS embossed with seal of the 'Royal Gardens Kew'. Letter has no valediction.</p>
               </note>July 9/69</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I write in haste by this mail, &amp; chiefly to say that your assistant Theodore<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Theodor Mueller; see M to J. Hooker, 6 September 1870 (in this edition as 70-09-06a). Wilhelm Sonder also helped him when he reached Hamburg; see W. Sonder to F. Krauss, 31 July 1869 (in this edition as M69-07-31).</p>
               </note> called 2 days ago on his way to Germany, having had his money stolen from him in Liverpool. I advanced the needful to him, &amp; showed him the Gardens. I am so glad that he could bring good news of your health. I congratulate you heartily on C.M.G. which I saw advertized in the Gazette.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.3299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Queen Victoria to M, 24 April 1869; the appointment was announced in a supplement to the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">London Gazette</seg>, 1 July 1869. For Hooker’s lobbying for Royal recognition for M, see Lucas (2013a), p. 19.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send you the <name key="Bilbergia">Bilbergia</name>s &amp; other <name key="Bromeliaceae">Bromeliaceae</name> at once.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Somersetshire has arrived with box 50 all safe in May.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sent by M on 6 March 1869 (Notebook recording despatch of plants for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora Australiensis</seg>, RB MSS M44, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lichens sent to Leighton with extracts from your letter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Books sent as requested &amp; parcels to Leyden &amp;c &amp;c<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 6 March 1869 (in this edition as 69-03-06a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Anglesey not arrived.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 17 April 1869 (in this edition as 69-04-17a). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bilbergia">Bilbergia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bromeliaceae">Bromeliaceae</name>
            </p>
